<item>
            <title>[FLINK-35522] The source task may get stuck after a failover occurs in batch jobs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-35522</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the source task does not get assigned a split because the SplitEnumerator has no more splits, and a failover occurs during the closing process, the SourceCoordinatorContext will not resend the NoMoreSplit event to the newly started source task, causing the source vertex to remain stuck indefinitely.&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
This case may only occur in batch jobs where speculative execution has been enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
